The paper deals with learning graphical models, which is a topic that falls under machine learning and statistics. The use of a structure penalty to learn the graph structure is a common technique in machine learning, which suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of potential functions and conditional independence structures, which are topics that fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of simulation studies and analysis of county data suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.ST (Statistics) sub-categories. Finally, the use of hierarchical function selection suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category.
